evidence: In CT, the radiation source is external - the X-ray tube outside the patient. In nuclear imaging, the source is internal - a radioactive tracer introduced into the bloodstream.
CT primarily gives anatomical information - structural details of organs and tissues.
Nuclear imaging, by contrast, provides functional information, showing how tissues are metabolizing or reacting biologically.
